RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 1 1M Turf CR: 81. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. (Non-Starters For A Claiming Price Of $40,000 Or Less In Their Last Starts Preferred). (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SMART MONIQUE bumped leaving the gate, showed early speed three deep then ceded command, raced keenly into the backstretch from off the rail, bid three deep at the quarter pole and proved best in the final sixteenth. CANDY ON TOP vied for the lead from inside then cleared outer rivals, showed the way to the far turn, challenged at the quarter pole, led to midstretch but got outfinished by SMART MONIQUE in deep stretch. SHEZMISBEHAVING came in and bumped leaving the gate, chased three then two wide early, three deep up the backstretch, spun four wide into the lane and rallied for the show. ELEGANCE CODE showed early speed four deep into the first turn then angled over to the two path, rated outside the leader in the middle stages, challenged two wide at the quarter pole, fought between rivals in the lane, then faltered in deep stretch. BOLD CHOICE vied between early then stalked from inside, saved ground through the far turn and never found room in the stretch run. TIZ MY PRINCESS got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, steered to the inside racing at the back early, got blocked behind a rival at the three-eighths pole, tipped two wide leaving that bend, moved out further in the drive and failed to menace. TAPIT ROCKS got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, settled two wide then along the rail, moved out and came three wide into the stretch and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, cleared, challenged 1/4, outfinished, 2nd best

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 67. Maiden Claiming Purse 34000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000, For Each $2,500 To $35,000 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS KALINE bumped with ONLY LIGHTNING at the start, set the pace from inside under pressure then cleared outer rivals on the backstretch, drifted out a bit at the quarter. PRESTIGIOUS trailed two wide early, moved into range then went inside a pair of rivals leaving the backstretch, saved ground around the second turn then entered the lane two wide, was no match for the winner in the furlong grounds but churned on to best the rest. JACQUELINE COCHRAN raced up close three deep early, chased outside a rival then three deep into the far turn, continued in the three path into the drive and flattened in the late stages. MAGIC CAPITAL stumbled leaving the gate, forwardly placed four deep into the first turn, trailed four wide into the far turn, moved out to the five path and remained wide into the lane and lacked a rally. ONLY LIGHTNING bumped leaving the gate, pressed between rivals early, chased the leader up the backstretch, started to weaken between foes on the far turn and tired in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 3 1M Turf CR: 85. Claiming Purse 37000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000, For Each $1,750 To $25,000 1 lb. (Rail at 20 feet).

CLAIM.OWNER: Little Red Feather Racing and Veranda Stables

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ICE QUEEN raced up close while keen early then stalked inside, tipped two wide on the far turn, surged to the front in upper stretch, led clear into the final sixteenth and held well. DOLLY MAY (IRE) allowed to fall back early and moved into the two path, swung out into the lane, closed widest in the stretch while drifting inward a bit late and proved second best. VIOLET STORM brushed leaving the gate, settled in the two path, went three wide into the far turn, moved out and entered the stretch five wide and got outkicked for the place honors. BALI DANCER bumped leaving the gate, sped to the front in the two path then cleared inside rival and moved over to the inside, set the pace under pressure to the far turn, vied inside rivals into the lane, lost command in upper stretch and flattened to fourth. CHEERFUL CHARM stalked the pace from inside then between into the backstretch, got boxed in between foes on the far turn then moved out and came three to four wide into the lane, raced behind traffic in upper stretch and failed to rally after gaining a clear path. SENSIBLE MOVE bumped at the start, tracked four wide early, raced in range three deep in the middle stages, bid three deep with a quarter mile left to run, could not kick on with the leader entering the final furlong and weakened. A CROWN FOR KITTEN settled inside, ran up behind rival at the quarter pole and could not rally once in the clear. LIZY D chased three wide early then went up to press the pace from outside, fought three deep into the lane and faded.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HORN OF PLENTY pressed the pace from inside then moved up on even terms with MONGOLIAN FORD, took over into the turn, put away MONGOLIAN FORD past the five-sixteenths pole, fought with ESTABLISHED into the lane, moved clear outside the eighth pole and inched away in late. ESTABLISHED broke a step slow, stalked the duo up the backstretch, bid three deep around the bend, lost touch with the leader in upper stretch and chased the winner to the wire while clearly second best. ITALIANO chased outside a rival early, went three wide into the bend, took aim four wide into the stretch and weakened. BOX OF CHOCOLATES chased along the rail to the stretch and weakened. MONGOLIAN FORD set the pace outside HORN OF PLENTY then dueled up the backstretch, lost command into the turn, kept the pressure on to the five-sixteenths pole, could not go on with the winner approaching the quarter pole and faded in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 5 6F Turf CR: 91. Maiden Special Weight Purse 67000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Cal-Bred or Cal-Sired horses Get a Five (5) Pound Weight Allowance. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TEENA ELLA away quickly, steadied and threw her head after crossing back onto the turn, ceded command from between rivals, moved to the inside stalking the top pair, tipped two wide into the stretch, moved out in the lane and drove clear. IRISH ROSE dropped back early, trailed on the inside into the turn, advanced along the fence through the bend, lacked room behind a rival and altered out in upper stretch, then rallied to gain the place. MAKE IT SNOW sat off the pace, went two wide into the turn, angled out and came four wide into the stretch, closed well through the lane and missed second. FOOLISH prompted the pace from outside early on, raced on even terms midway around the bend, took over leaving the turn, cleared briefly in upper stretch but was soon challenged from outside, relinquished the lead in midstretch and flattened in the final sixteenth. IRISH PATSY got bothered from outside and steadied briefly early, went two wide around the turn, three wide into the stretch, lugged in near the eighth pole and could not rally. WUDI set the pace under pressure from outside rival, dueled around the turn, lost command approaching the stretch and weakened. CRIMSON SONATA stalked the top pair off the rail into the turn, spun three wide into the lane and weakened. CARSON JEN threw her head and hopped slightly at the start but still came away with the field, reserved in the early stages near the inside then two wide on the turn, raced between leaving the bend and weakened under minimal asking. DISRUPTIVE ARTIST was off slow from outside, raced three wide into the turn, trailed two wide into the stretch and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SKINNER settled two to three wide off the pace, moved closer nearing the far turn, gained four then three wide around the bend, took over in upper stretch, kicked clear from YELLOW BRICK and won going away under mild asking. TEXTHELEGEND tracked two wide into the first turn then moved out four wide around the bend, chased three then two wide on the second bend, steadied behind YELLOW BRICK in upper stretch, moved out and edged that rival for second. YELLOW BRICK showed early speed from inside then chased the leader around the first turn, moved off the rail then went between to challenge for command, vied up the backstretch, held a short lead into the far turn, moved clear past the five-sixteenths pole, challenged by the winner at the top of the lane, could not offer any resistance and got edged for the place honors. I DON'T GET IT stumbled badly at the start, raced on the inside off the pace, went between rivals at the three-eighths pole, spun three wide into the lane, moved out further in the drive and kept on for a minor award. RIVERSIDE stalked on the inside into the first turn, moved out and went three wide into the backstretch, vied three deep in the middle stages, kept the pressure on to the five-sixteenths pole then lost contact and chased along the rail into the lane and weakened. HORNUNG was off slow to begin and never got invovled. SPEED OF THE NILE showed keen early speed four wide then cleared and angled in around the first turn, vied with a pair of rivals up the backstretch, dropped back on the far turn and had little left in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 7 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Claiming Purse 24000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPOILED ROTTEN vied for command between rivals, dueled outside SUGAR SUGAR past the five-sixteenths pole, put that rival away past the sixteenth pole and gamely prevailed over the late challenge from the runner-up. SAPADILLA stalked the speedy trio outside a rival, spun three wide into the lane, rallied and drew alongside SPOILED ROTTEN in the final sixteenth but could not get by. SUGAR SUGAR vied inside a pair of rivals to the turn, dueled past the five-sixteenths pole, battled through the lane and flattened in the final sixteenth. VEGAS DREAM was antsy in the gate, vied for the lead three deep early, could not keep pace past the five-sixteenths marker, chased two wide into the drive and weakened. MACHO QUEEN bumped with inner rival at the start, checked off heels early, saved ground then tipped out at the top of the lane and improved position. LADY DERBY antsy in the starting gate, checked between rivals nearing the half-mile pole, went three then four wide on the turn and came up empty in the drive. CAT BANDIT climbed early behind the field, went two to three wide on the turn and failed to menace. MENSA ON TAP bumped in the beginning, stalked the top trio on the inside and faded in the lane. AMAGE coaxed from the gate early, chased outside rivals and got bothered from inside approaching the half-mile pole, rounded the bend four then five wide and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Lady of Shamrock S. SANTA ANITA PARK RACE 8 1M Turf CR: 91. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLD FILLIES. By subscription of $100 each if made on or before Thursday, February 2, 2023, closed with 19 or by Supplementary nomination of $2,000 due at time of entry. $750 to enter and an additional $750 to start with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner, $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth and $2,000 to fifth. Weight 124 lbs. Non-Winners of a Sweepstakes at One Mile or over allowed 2 lbs. Non-Winners of A Race other than Maiden, Claiming or Starter at One Mile or Over allowed 4 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AG BULLET brushed the gate but was still away in good order, showed early speed then was taken in hand and rated behind the leader from inside, bid two wide at the five-sixteenths pole, took over then cleared in upper stretch and held gamely in the closing moments. THE WILD GRAZER (IRE) tracked in the two path, went three deep into the far turn, bumped with TEA N CONVERSTATION entering the stretch, chased into the final sixteenth, then launched a late bid but ran out of time. PRINCESS BETTINA bumped into the first turn while in the two path, settled off the pace, went between runners in middle stages, had to pause when boxed in three deep entering the far turn, tipped out into the clear and was roused four wide around the bend, rallied from outside in the lane and gained the show. TEA N CONVERSATION unhurried in the early going and moved inside, bumped with outer rival into the first turn, went between rivals at the half-mile pole, brushed with NYVAN at the five-sixteenths pole, bumped with outer rival into the stretch, then finished willingly in the final furlong for a minor award. NYVAN pulled along the inside early then settled in range, brushed with TEA N CONVERSATION at the five-sixteenths pole, stayed inside to the stretch and could not rally. BROADWAY GIRLS sped clear and crossed over to the inside, showed the way up the backstretch, pressured from outside at the five-sixteenths marker, dueled into the lane, lost command in upper stretch and weakened in the furlong grounds. QUICKLY PARK IT traveled three deep early at the back, went four deep into the far turn, dropped back to last and angled down to the two path, eased in the lane and walked off.
